{
  "stem": "2522.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "To get a presidential exemption, a so-called white card, which exempted you from deportation as an economically essential Jew for the Slovak Republic, you had to have a sponsor.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my father from his days at the-- in the district council became very well acquainted and good friends with two priests who were very influential-- Father Bronecky, the, the Catholic priest and Senior Zeman, the head of the Evangelical Church.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He went to them and said, you know, what can I do?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And Bronecky, who was a good friend and senior to, to [INAUDIBLE], the president, suggested that baptism would greatly improve the chances of, of, of getting a white card.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that he personally would intervene.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Catholic baptism was very, very difficult to execute.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It took a long time.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So an agreement was reached that an Evangelical baptism of the Lutheran church would be the solution.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so within three months after bar mitzvah, which I was in January 24, 1942-- within three months, I started studying Catechism in order to prepare for a formal baptism which took place, I believe in June of 1942, in the middle of the deportation.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Within weeks my father received a white card, which protected him and his family, and also applied to his own parents, which was really the key.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Immediately, they changed our position because after the end of the deportations in September of 1942-- cessation of deportation-- the Jewish population in Trencin was brought down to less than 4% of the pre-war population.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And because I was baptized, following procedures, I was able to go back to school.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so I was admitted to the Catholic school as a student, and was treated just like everybody else.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
